1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:05,158
When you start the activities, they will follow the same order as this lesson.

2
00:00:05,108 --> 00:00:10,095
First, you do a warm-up: You select a word, then clicks away.

3
00:00:10,095 --> 00:00:14,116
Repeat until choose first, change second is clear.

4
00:00:14,116 --> 00:00:18,695
Then you answer quick checks, so we know the key words make sense.

5
00:00:18,695 --> 00:00:26,127
Next, you practise the real computer skill: Apply bold, italic and underline to three different words.

6
00:00:26,127 --> 00:00:28,668
Undo one and apply it again.

7
00:00:28,668 --> 00:00:34,211
You may also type a short answer, for example: Type the rule for formatting.

8
00:00:34,211 --> 00:00:42,703
At the end, you finish with a stretch or reflection: You formats a three-line note so the title stands out and key words are readable.

9
00:00:42,703 --> 00:00:45,268
Take one activity at a time.

10
00:00:45,268 --> 00:00:49,823
If you need help, ask staff, then try the next step yourself.

